20
00:01:07,350 --> 00:01:10,520
The clinical symptoms of Bronchitis really
center on cough.

21
00:01:10,520 --> 00:01:13,490
It's a productive cough and can last for
several weeks.

22
00:01:13,490 --> 00:01:17,870
The cough is due to attempts of clearing
the secretions caused by inflammation of

23
00:01:17,870 --> 00:01:20,090
the mucus membrane of the bronchi.

24
00:01:20,090 --> 00:01:24,010
Sometimes the secretions in speed-um can
appear virulent, but

25
00:01:24,010 --> 00:01:27,530
this does not mean that the patient has a
bacterial infection.

26
00:01:27,530 --> 00:01:31,510
The perelence is from sluffing cells mixed
with mucus.

27
00:01:31,510 --> 00:01:34,720
In this case because it is not a bacterial
infection,

28
00:01:34,720 --> 00:01:37,460
you do not need to give the patient
antibiotics.

29
00:01:37,460 --> 00:01:42,030
In fact Bronchitis is one of the leading
diagnoses of inappropriate antibiotic use.

30
00:01:42,030 --> 00:01:44,120
Bronchitis is predominantly a viral
infection, and

31
00:01:44,120 --> 00:01:47,520
most of the respiratory viruses that we've
been discussing can cause it.

32
00:01:47,520 --> 00:01:50,250
Only a few bacteria can cause bronchitis.

33
00:01:50,250 --> 00:01:52,810
Inflammation of the Bronchi can cause
Bronco spasms so

34
