35
00:01:55,380 --> 00:01:59,000
However fever and systemic symptoms are
unusual.

36
00:01:59,000 --> 00:02:01,320
And, if you see these in your patient,

37
00:02:01,320 --> 00:02:05,790
another diagnosis should be thought about
including influenza and pneumonia.

38
00:02:06,940 --> 00:02:09,220
Now, we're going to discuss Bronchiolitis.

39
00:02:09,220 --> 00:02:10,480
This is the inflammation of

40
00:02:10,480 --> 00:02:13,580
the Bronchioles that are narrower than
bronchi.

41
00:02:13,580 --> 00:02:16,350
Any of the viruses that we have discussed
can cause Bronchilitis but

42
00:02:16,350 --> 00:02:17,960
the hallmark virus is RSV.

43
00:02:19,160 --> 00:02:23,280
Bronchiolitis mostly affects infants and
young children, and has a 4 to 6 day

44
00:02:23,280 --> 00:02:27,420
incubation period which is when the virus
colonizes the infant asymptotically.

45
00:02:27,420 --> 00:02:31,870
The upper respiratory infection symptoms
and fever manifest once the innate immune

46
00:02:31,870 --> 00:02:36,660
system recognized the virus and initiates
production and secretions of citocons.

47
00:02:36,660 --> 00:02:41,170
A third of the infants and young children
with RSV infection will progress to lower

48
00:02:41,170 --> 00:02:43,390
respiratory tract disease.

49
00:02:43,390 --> 00:02:46,690
And the patient will have fast breathing
or tachypnea,

50
00:02:46,690 --> 00:02:51,640
coughing, and respiratory distress with
retractions and wheezing.

51
00:02:51,640 --> 00:02:52,680
Here is a video of a baby with RSV
Bronchiolitis.

52
00:02:52,680 --> 00:02:55,473
